1. Research potential target banks and their daily routines.
2. Obtain a gun and ammunition.
3. Wear clothing that allows for easy movement and concealment of the gun.
4. Choose a time when the bank is likely to have a high volume of customers.
5. Enter the bank with confidence and avoid drawing attention to yourself.
6. Approach the teller and demand money and/or valuables.
7. Do not show any hesitation or uncertainty.
8. If there are other people in the bank, keep your voice low and avoid drawing attention to yourself.
9. If alarms are triggered, do not panic and try to leave the bank as quickly as possible.
10. If confronted by security personnel, do not resist and surrender immediately.